 difference in sterility due to high temperature during the flowering period among japonica rice varieties (2001) Plant Production Science, 4, pp. 90-93. , doi:10.1626/pps.4.90; Matsushima, S., Ikewada, H., Maeda, A., Honma, S., Niki, H., Study on rice cultivation in the tropics. 1. Yielding and ripening response of the rice plant to the extremely hot and dry climate in Sudan (1982) Japanese Journal of Tropical Agriculture, 26, pp. 19-25; Morokuma, M., Yasuda, S., Effects of high temperature and high humidity during the flowering period on spikelet fertility in japonica rice (2004) Japanese Journal of Crop Science, 73 (1), pp. 93-98. , DOI 10.1626/jcs.73.93; Morokuma, M., Yajima, M., Yonemura, S., Effects of elevated CO2 concentration and warming on growth and yield of rice (1996) Japanese Journal of Crop Science, 65 (2), pp. 222-228; Nakagawa, H., Horie, T., Matsui, T., Effects of climate change on rice production and adaptive technologies (2002) Rice Science: Innovations and Impact for Livelihood, pp. 635-657. , (Eds TW Mew, DS Brar, S Peng, D Dawe, B Hardy) (International Rice Research Institute: China); Oh-e, I., Saitoh, K., Kuroda, T., Effects of high temperature on growth, yield and dry-matter production of rice grown in the paddy field (2007) Plant Production Science, 10 (4), pp. 412-422. , http://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/pps/10/4/412/_pdf, DOI 10.1626/pps.10.412; Osada, A., Sasiprapa, V., Rahong, M., Dhammanuvong, S., Chakrabondho, H., Abnormal occurrence of empty grains of indica rice plants in the dry, hot season in Thailand (1973) Proceedings Crop Science Society of Japan, 42, pp. 103-109; Prasad, P.V.V., Boote, K.J., Allen Jr., L.H., Sheehy, J.E., Thomas, J.M.G., Species, ecotype and cultivar differences in spikelet fertility and harvest index of rice in response to high temperature stress (2006) Field Crops Research, 95 (2-3), pp. 398-411. , DOI 10.1016/j.fcr.2005.04.008, PII S0378429005000924; Satake, T., Yoshida, S., High temperature induced steri